# Respond to automated PR reviewers (Gemini Code Assist, Codex, similar)

**Substantive feedback** definition and merge timing: **`git-pr-workflow-default.mdc`** (“PR review bots”, **Bot feedback wait gate**). **Never** merge or enable auto-merge the instant CI turns green—complete that gate first (or explicit waiver).

Treat repo **automated code-review** output as mandatory communication follow-up—not optional—especially:

- **Google Gemini Code Assist** (`gemini-code-assist`)
- **Codex** when it appears as an automated reviewer

Similar bots (summaries, inline comments, suggestion blocks) are included unless listed in **Exceptions**.

## Required (each substantive point you own)

1. **Reply in-thread** on the comment or review summary—not only pushes.
2. Label **implemented** (what/SHA), **deferred** (why; optional `docs/REFACTOR_BACKLOG.md`), or **declined** (merit-based).
3. Prefer a small follow-up commit when straightforward; explicit **defer** / **decline** must appear in-thread.

Do **not** merge with substantive Gemini or Codex feedback **unanswered**.

## Exceptions

- **SKIPPED** / rate-limited empty / purely informational with no actionable claim: reply optional (“skipped”).
- Already covered upstream: one bundled reply is fine.

## Vs CI

Green **`ci_result`** does **not** replace threaded closure.

## Rationale

Auditable reviews; separates acknowledgement from silent dismissal.
